>The later "success" of the Bulge attack 
>was partially due to Hitler's suspicions that the code had indeed been 
>compromised. He therefor bypassed the ordinary method of passing orders to 
>the field. An ill-fated offensive, but it DID catch us by surprise.

Can you cite a source for the claim that Hitler's suspicions
that enigma had been compromised played a role in not using it for
passing orders related to the Ardennes offensive?

(I knew he had bypassed using the enigma but thought the
reasons were other than concerns about enigma security).

